WHO   — WORDS OUTLIVE THEIR REASONS — a PHONETIKOS entry
WHAT  — WORDS OUTLIVE THEIR REASONS — the universe's keystone message: we speak fossils daily, and reading them is why PHONETIKOS exists.
WHERE — every ordinary sentence, where obsolete gods, machines, and beliefs are still spoken unawares  Framework inputs: the OED; standard etymological references; the literature on semantic change & drift  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — because usage is inherited whole and the reason is not — the form outlives the meaning, so the mouth preserves what the culture forgot.
HOW   — a word keeps being used long after the world that justified it is gone, carrying a fossilised reason no living speaker intends.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  Every time you say goodbye you say a prayer you no longer believe — words outlive their reasons.

